<ptxt>
There are two types of colored wire used in this vehicle. One is single-colored type and the other is dual-colored (striped) type.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
The single-colored type of wire uses only one color symbol (i.e. “GRN”).
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
The dual-colored type of wire uses two color symbols (i.e. “GRN/YEL”). The first symbol represents the base color of the wire (“GRN” in the figure) and the second symbol represents the color of the stripe (“YEL” in the figure).
</ptxt>
